data set is a vector point digital data structure that  contains the locations of General Public Use Airports in the State of New Mexico. It only contains those airports that the New Mexico State Highway and Transportation Department inspects. The point represents the center of the land owned by the airport.</abstract>          <purpose>To show the general locations of public airports in the state of New Mexico.</purpose>       </descript>       <timeperd>          <timeinfo>             <sngdate>                <caldate>19980519</caldate>             </sngdate>          </timeinfo>          <current>publication date</current>       </timeperd>       <status>          <progress>Complete</progress>          <update>As needed</update>       </status>       <spdom>          <bounding>             <westbc>-108.867904663086</westbc>             <eastbc>-103.079795837402</eastbc>             <northbc>36.9278106689453</northbc>             <southbc>31.8811054229736</southbc>          </bounding>       </spdom>       <keywords>          <theme>             <themekt>ISO 19115 Topic Categories</themekt>             <themekey>transportation</themekey>          </theme>          <theme>             <themekt>none</themekt>             <themekey>Airports</themekey>             <themekey>Aviation</themekey>             <themekey>NM airports</themekey>          </theme>          <place>             <placekt>Spatial Reference System Identifiers</placekt>             <placekey>EPSG:4269</placekey>             <placekey>EPSG:7019</placekey>          </place>          <place>             <placekt>none</placekt>             <placekey>New Mexico</placekey>          </place>       </keywords>       <accconst>None</accconst>       <useconst>Resource Geographic Information System (RGIS) Program assumes no liability for misuse of the data. They were used to generate a digital file of points using  ArcView.  The resulting shapefile was attributed in  ARCVIEW from the same chart and then converted to an ARC/INFO coverage using the shapearc command. Visual inspection of point location against a backdrop of major roads was conducted to verify location accuracy.</procdesc>             <procdate>19980519</procdate>             <proccont>
